INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (99, 22, 'project_manager', 'Make sure whoever is actually creating the project is involved in this step! It\'ll help your Content Developer and Design Lead immensely to get to know the personality of the client as  thoroughly as possible (without playing telephone).\r\n\r\nThe Project Manager should set up an FTP / RELAY (<a href="http://relay.duarte.com" target="_blank">http://relay.duarte.com</a>) login for the Client, and e-mail the log in and password them.\r\n\r\nFor Studio / Studio Lite projects, create and distribute the Project Contact List with names and contact info for Clients, as well as key Duarte personnel (President, Vice President, Account Director, Account Manager, Project Manager). Artifact: EX_Key Contacts List.docx\r\n\r\nIdentify the client\'s technical requirements (the Account Manager may already have them) and distribute this information to the relevant creative teams. Use the Client Technical Requirements artifact for reference. Artifact: IN_Technological Requirements.docx\r\n\r\nIf the Project Manager will be traveling for the project, s/he should communicate with the Office Manager/Travel Agent to make the necessary arrangements. Review the Travel Checklist to make sure you cover all your bases. Artifact: IN_Travel Checklist.docx\r\n\r\nProvide all source materials to the internal team prior to the Collaborative Discovery Session and/or kickoff. Review the Internal Kickoff Checklist to ensure all possible issues are considered in the Internal Kickoff Meeting. Artifact: IN_Kickoff Checklist.docx\r\n\r\nFormulate the Internal Kickoff Summary document, and distribute it to all internal team members. This document identifies all relevant issues and questions to pose to Client, and should be used to help formulate the agenda(s) for the Collaborative Discovery Session. Artifact: IN_Kickoff Summary.docx') ; 
