INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (2465, 218, 'project_manager', 'Before the invoice can be sent, the Project Manager must verify: hours and rates (including contractors), rush time, purchased images, working meals and other expenses, delivery email confirmation.\r\n\r\nFor out of pocket expense incurred during the project, the Project Manager should complete a Duarte Expense Report, tape/staple the receipts for expenses to the Report, then submit to their Account Manager for signature. Artifact: IN_Expense_Report.xls\r\n\r\nTo begin processing the invoice, the Project Manager should submit a Billing Sheet to Accounting, making sure to highlight any special requests. Artifact:  Billing_Sheet_Highlight_AP.jpg\r\n\r\nTo ensure accuracy of the Billing Sheet, make sure all appropriate fields (Contact Info, Phase, Delivered Via, Terms, Invoice # relating to any prebills, etc.) are completed in FileMaker. Artifact: Billing_Sheet_Fields.jpg\r\n\r\nIf the Client would prefer the invoice to be delivered as a PDF via e-mail, you must specify this in the Declarations field of the Billing Sheet. If no specific request is made in the Declarations portion of the Billing Sheet, Accounting will send the invoice to the client via regular mail.\r\n\r\nWhen it\'s time to submit the Final Invoice (vs. a Prebill or Milestone Bill), adjust the Billing Sheet to request that Accounting "Close and Archive" the job once payment is received. This change can be made in FileMaker. Artifact: Close_Archive.jpg') ; 
