INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (3012, 294, 'project_manager', 'Communicate regularly with Art Direction / Content Developers/ MultiMedia (all internal service bureaus) in terms of how much content budget is remaining on their project(s), and CC the Content Project Manager.\r\n\r\nWhen scoping a project and inquiring about the availability and/or budget estimation of art director / content resources, first send an email TO: Content Project Manager and CC: Patti and Diandra, respectively, on ALL requests. In the subject line, please indicate Job #, Client Name, if a New Client please note, and the response time needed. In the email, please include the following information: approximate timeline, anticipated budget / range, skillsset (art director / content) needed. This will streamline and organize communications so they can respond to you more effectively. A meeting may be required to finalize, depending upon complexity of request.\r\n\r\nArt Directors should be consulted on who they feel would be the most successful at leading the design aspect of the project and why.\r\n\r\nIf the likelihood of a project is 60% or better, you may request a HOLD on a content resource. These requests are handled by the Creative Project Manager.\r\n\r\nIf there is a change in project status, the burden is on the Project Manager to tell Creative Project Manager as soon as possible. If there is a change in resource status, the burden is on the Creative Project Manager to tell the Project Manager as soon as possible.') ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (3013, 294, 'account_manager', 'Account Manager conducts a Client Needs Assessment to identify client pain points and recommend possible Duarte solutions. The Discovery Questions document is a good tool to use for a more strategic approach. Artifact: EX_Discovery Questions.docx\r\n\r\nAM formulates SOW summaring project purpose, scope, budget / schedule, and list of deliverables for client review. Artifacts: EX_Studio SOW.docx and EX_Studio_proposal.docx\r\n\r\nAny Duarte resource HOLD dates should be stated in the SOW in a form similar to: "The Schedule promised in the Statement of Work expires on (insert date) due to resource availability."') ; 
