INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (3285, 313, 'project_manager', 'Project Managers should communicate regularly with Art Direction / Content Developers/ MultiMedia in terms of how much content budget is remaining on their project(s), and CC the Content Project Manager.\r\n\r\nWhen scoping a project and inquiring about the availability and/or budget estimation of art director / content resources.\r\n\r\nFirst send an email.\r\nTO: Content Project Manager\r\nCC: Patti and Diandra, respectively, on ALL requests.\r\n\r\n<strong>In the subject line,</strong> please indicate Job #, Client Name, if a New Client please note, and the response time needed.\r\n\r\n<strong>In the body of the email,</strong> please include the following information:\r\nApproximate timeline\r\nAnticipated budget / range\r\nSkillsset (art director / content) needed\r\n\r\nThis will streamline and organize communications so they can respond to you more effectively. A meeting may be required to finalize, depending upon complexity of request.\r\n\r\nArt Directors should be consulted on who they feel would be the most successful at leading the design aspect of the project and why.\r\n\r\nIf the likelihood of a project is 60% or better, you may request a HOLD on a content resource. These requests are handled by the Creative Project Manager.\r\n\r\nIf there is a change in project status, the burden is on the Project Manager to tell the Creative Project Manager as soon as possible. If there is a change in resource status, the burden is on the Creative Project Manager to tell the Project Manager as soon as possible.') ; 
