INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (3582, 341, 'project_manager', '<span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">When scoping a project and inquiring about the availability and/or budget estimation of Art Director / Content resources, f</span><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">irst send an email:</span>\r\n\r\nTO: Content Project Manager\r\nCC: Patti and Diandra (on ALL requests)\r\n\r\n<strong>In the subject line,</strong> indicate Job #, Client Name, and response time needed. If it\'s a new Client, be sure to mention that.\r\n\r\n<strong style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">In the body of the email,</strong><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;"> please include the following information:</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.714285714;">Approximate timeline</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.714285714;">Anticipated budget range</span>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Skill set needed </span><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">(Art director / Content)</span>\r\n\r\nThis initial e-mail will streamline and organize communications so they can respond to you more effectively. A meeting may be required to finalize the team and timeline, depending upon complexity of request.\r\n\r\nArt Directors should be consulted on who they feel would be the most successful at leading the design aspect of the project and why.\r\n\r\nIf the likelihood of a project is 60% or better, you may request a HOLD on a content resource. These requests are handled by the Creative Project Manager.\r\n\r\nIf there is a change in project status, the burden is on the Project Manager to tell the Creative Project Manager as soon as possible. If there is a change in resource status, the burden is on the Creative Project Manager to tell the Project Manager as soon as possible.') ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (3583, 341, 'account_manager', 'At the outset of the project, the Account Manager conducts a Client Needs Assessment to identify client pain points and recommend possible Duarte solutions. The Discovery Questions document is a good tool to use for a more strategic approach. <strong><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Artifact: EX_Discovery Questions.docx</span></em></strong>\r\n\r\nThe Account Manager should confirm technology requirements with client.\r\n\r\nThe Account Manager formulates a Statement of Work (SOW) summarizing the project purpose, scope, budget, schedule, and list of deliverables for client review. Artifacts: EX_Studio SOW and EX_Studio Proposal\r\n\r\nIf any Duarte resources are being held for this project, HOLD dates should be stated in the SOW in a form similar to: "The Schedule promised in the Statement of Work expires on [insert date] due to resource availability."') ; 
