INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (4606, 442, 'account_manager', 'The process of setting up an NDA goes like this:\r\n\r\n1. Discussion about the NDA with the prospective Client\r\n\r\n2. Receive the NDA document from the Client, pass to Contract Administrator, CC President\r\n\r\n3. The Contract Administrator reviews and approves or edits the NDA. The Client\'s legal team may intervene, at which point the Contract Administrator will negotiate. This continues until both sides agree.\r\n\r\n4A. If the NDA is not approved, close the project.\r\n\r\n4B. If the NDA is approved, send the NDA to the President for signature. (If the President is unavailable to sign in a timely fashion, send to Mark Duarte, then Nancy Duarte, in that order.)\r\n\r\n5. Once signed, the NDA should be returned to the Account Manager.\r\n\r\n6. Account Manager sends Duarte-executed NDA to Client.\r\n\r\n7. Once the Client returns the signed document, attach a PDF of the fully signed document in FileMaker.') ; 
