INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (11597, 1067, 'project_manager', 'When scoping a project and inquiring about the availability and/or budget estimation of Art Director / Content resources, first send an email:\r\n<pre>TO: Traffic Coordinator (responsible for Art Directors and Content Team)\r\nCC: patti@duarte.com, diandra@duarte.com (on ALL requests)</pre>\r\nIn the subject line, indicate:\r\n<pre>Job #\r\nClient\'s company name\r\nResponse time needed\r\n(Oh and if it\'s a new Client, be sure to mention that.)</pre>\r\nIn the body of the email, please include:\r\n<pre>Approximate timeline\r\nAnticipated budget range\r\nSkill set needed (Art Director / Content)</pre>\r\nThis initial e-mail will streamline communication so the Traffic Coordinator can respond to you more effectively. Depending upon the complexity of the request, a meeting may be required to finalize the team and timeline.\r\n\r\nArt Directors should be consulted on who they feel would be the most successful at leading the design aspect of the project and why.\r\n\r\nIf the likelihood of the project is 60% or better, you may request to HOLD a Content resource.\r\n\r\nIf there is a change in <em>project status,</em> the burden is on the Project Manager to tell the Traffic Coordinator as soon as possible. If there is a change in <em>resource status</em>, the burden is on the Traffic Coordinator to tell the Project Manager as soon as possible.') ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (11598, 1067, 'account_manager', 'At the outset of the project, the Account Manager should conduct a Client Needs Assessment to identify the Client\'s pain points, and recommend possible Duarte solutions. The <a href="http://172.16.0.20/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IN_Discovery-Questions.dotx">Discovery Questions</a> document is a good tool to use for a more strategic approach.\r\n\r\nAs soon as possible, the Account Manager should confirm technology requirements with client. (Mac or PC, PPT or Keynote, A/V equipment, etc.)\r\n\r\nUsing the information they\'ve gathered, the Account Manager should formulate a Statement of Work (SOW) for the Client\'s review, summarizing the project purpose, scope, budget, schedule, and list of deliverables. See: <a href="http://172.16.0.20/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/EX_Studio-SOW.dotx">Studio SOW</a> and <a href="http://172.16.0.20/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/EX_Studio_Proposal.dotx">Studio Proposal</a>\r\n\r\nIf any Duarte resources are being held for this project, the HOLD dates should be stated in the SOW in a form similar to: "The Schedule promised in the Statement of Work expires on [insert date] due to resource availability."') ; 
