INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (12430, 1127, 'designer', 'This is one of the most creative parts of the process! Don\'t feel like you need to sit at your desk to do it. Grab a couch, or a table at your local coffee shop.\r\n\r\nYou may find that having more than two or three people in a storyboarding brainstorm session can very quickly slow down the process.\r\n\r\nThe process of developing the Storyboard usually flows like this:\r\n1) Brainstorm. If it\'s done on a white board, be sure to snap a photo so you can refer to it later. PRO TIP: If you don\'t want someone to erase your masterpiece, write SAVE UNTIL [desired date] on it, or it\'ll be erased real quick.\r\n2) Design Lead formulates cheap and easy sketches based on the brainstorm. (Don\'t spend too long on \'em, 1 hour max.)\r\n3) Design Lead pitches storyboard to internal team.\r\n4) Design Lead receives and incorporates feedback.\r\n5) Design Lead pitches revised storyboard to internal team.\r\n6) Design Lead makes final round of edits and drops slides into a PowerPoint template.\r\n7) Design Lead and the internal team do a final review to finalize the Storyboard before presenting it to the Client.\r\n\r\nIf you want to save <em>tons</em> of time, execute your storyboards digitally in Adobe Illustrator using a Wacom Tablet or a Cintiq monitor. You\'ll save yourself from spending hours of time scanning, cropping, and color-correcting.') ; 
